<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, for your information do you realize Druids can solo in POT with very very little risk. Fighting in a full group in Tactics alone is hard at times....let alone soloing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Again I don't particularly care what druids can solo.  Maybe they are unfairly powerful in those zones, in which case that needs to be addressed with changes to the zone or changes to the druid class.  <br>
<br>
For every time you pull an example of an Enchanter soloing a BoT mini or a Druid soloing in Tactics you can find an example of a Rogue being unable to solo a light blue in a tier 1 zone.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Goladus: DID I SAY <br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
&quot;If anyone should be soloing Mini-bosses, it should be mages, not Enchanters.<br>
<br>
Mages should be the most powerful class in the game. <br>
<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
If not, then dont try to throw words in my mouth. I said exactly what I wanted to say. No more and no less.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->No, that's not what you said.  I apologize for putting words in your mouth.  This is what you said:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As of now any one that says Mages shouldnt/couldnt get certain things because it would overpower us,,,,should be slapped. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->which means you could ask for a 70% slow and get away with it.<br>
<br>
If there is an overpowered ability in the game, the best answer isn't to ruin the whole game by powering up everyone else.  This constant charm bitching only points to charm needing to be nerfed, it does not justify any single magician upgrade.  To what extent charm needs adjustment is a completely different debate.<br>
<br>
Indeed pointing out any isolated incidents of isolated accomplishments says either 1.  someone skilled was playing and there is no problem, or 2. that class has an overpowered ability, whether situationally or in general.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, there are so many classes that solo, which is another point, but you dismiss that in every thread I read. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And you continually ignore that there are many classes that can not solo even as well as magicians.  How is it fair to them to ask for soloing upgrades?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Me pointing out a class Soloing a Mini-Boss was more of giving out information and how I felt. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Which is as much your right as is my right to disagree with you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, how Im tired I am of Magicians like you turning a topic around to try to say Magicians dont need any type of upgrade or extra abilities to put us on par with other classes that can solo.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And I am tired of you trying to say that we <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>need</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> something to help our solo ability.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Note: every class that can solo are a viable substitute for damage also in a group setting. So that &quot;Damage output of Magicians&quot; BS just dont cut it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Mage damage &gt; Druid damage.  Mage damage ~ Wizard Damage.  Mage Damage ~ Necro Damage, Even Mage Damage &gt; Enchanter Damage unless the enchanter is charming and the mage is not.  If both are charming mage probably still does more damage.  Mage Damage &gt; Bard Damage.  Mage Damage &gt; Shaman Damage<br>
<br>
And what of the classes that can't solo?<br>
<br>
Mage Damage &gt; Warrior Damage<br>
Mage Damage &gt; Rogue Damage<br>
Mage Damage &gt; Monk Damage<br>
Mage Damage &gt; Paladin Damage<br>
Mage Damage &gt;~ Shadowknight Damage<br>
<br>
So it boils down to what, Wizards outsolo us and outdamage us in groups if we can't use charm, Enchanters and Druids outsolo us and outdamage us if we can.  No one else except possibly Necromancers and Rogues can outdamage us in groups, and if rogues solo at all they are far worse at it than we are.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They have been saying that COD is too powerful and something will be done. How long does it take? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Here is the problem with fixing charm.<br>
<br>
It is fairly apparent that several encounters are designed to require charm, or at least charm is supposed to be a viable and powerful ability for that encounter.  After spending most of Velious casting buffs and the occaisional slow, and luclin mobs having sideshow gimmick adds spawned to keep chanters occupied, they deserve a chance to be powerful.  They need to find a solution that will fix the charm balance without making it useless or unfun.<br>
<br>
Do mages deserve something similar, something fun to put us in the spotlight on raids?  Sure!  If that has the side-effect of making us better soloers?  No problem at all!  We aren't going to get there bitching about Charm, though.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Just ignore Goladus, he makes all kinds of odd statements, like claiming his pets somehow last 60 seconds against pop mobs. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I never made this claim.  I said that my level 34 earth pet lasted 60 seconds against a cat in Overthere, which wasn't much longer than how long my 61 air pet lasts against the mobs I solo, which as I had made clear in that thread were Trash mobs in PoD and PoN.  And actually, against Wanton Tronera's in plane of storms my pet lasts a lot longer than 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Charms will get nerfed eventually.<br>
<br>
Would be nice if things were play tested more. nerfs for any class are not cool. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I would have to agree with rthen, and mage charm is no less of a problem than the charms of other classes. <p><center><br>
